Notes.Text:
This update for expat fixes the following issues:

- CVE-2023-52425: Fixed a DoS caused by processing large tokens. (bsc#1219559) 
- CVE-2024-28757: Fixed an XML Entity Expansion. (bsc#1221289)

Notes.Title: Patchnames

Vulnerabilities.Description: libexpat through 2.5.0 allows a denial of service (resource consumption) because many full reparsings are required in the case of a large token for which multiple buffer fills are needed.
libexpat through 2.6.1 allows an XML Entity Expansion attack when there is isolated use of external parsers (created via XML_ExternalEntityParserCreate).
